    "caveat": "When operated in FIPS mode",
    "description": "The PICOfreedom provides FIPS 140-2 Approved security functionality to DiskOnKey USB flash drives. The PICOfreedom employs Federal Information Processing Standard (FIPS 140-2) encryption and key management functionality to ensure the protection of data stored on FLASH memory. The module is a multi-chip standalone cryptographic module, as defined by FIPS 140-2, and consists of the S2 controller and an EEPROM. Both components are encased in a hard, opaque, production grade integrated circuit packaging.",
